            <div class="article-content fs-5 lh-lg">
                <p class="lead fw-normal text-secondary mb-4">
                    In the world of Olympic Weightlifting, names like Suleymanoglu and Dimas are spoken of with reverence. Today, a new name has joined that pantheon: <strong>Karlos Nasar.</strong>
                </p>

                <h2 class="fw-bold mt-5 mb-3">The Paris 2024 Explosion</h2>
                <p>
                    The atmosphere inside the South Paris Arena was electric. Going into the 89kg category, the world knew Nasar was the favorite, but nobody expected the clinical precision he displayed. With a successful 180kg Snatch, he set the stage for his signature move: the Clean & Jerk.
                </p>

                <blockquote class="blockquote border-start border-4 border-primary ps-4 my-5 py-2 bg-light italic">
                    "I don't just lift for myself; I lift for the history of Bulgaria and for everyone who believes that limits are meant to be broken."
                    <footer class="blockquote-footer mt-2">Karlos Nasar after his 224kg lift</footer>
                </blockquote>

                <p>
                    When the weight was loaded to 224kg—a world record attempt—the room went silent. Nasar approached the bar with a calm that defied his 20 years of age. The clean was effortless; the jerk was a masterpiece of power and stability. When the three white lights flashed, a new Olympic and World Record was born.
                </p>

                <h2 class="fw-bold mt-5 mb-3">Recent Wins & Dominance</h2>
                <p>
                    Nasar’s journey hasn't been without hurdles. After a freak injury in 2023 that threatened his career, his comeback has been nothing short of miraculous. 
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>2025 World Championships:</strong> Claimed his third World Title in a third weight class (94kg) with a 395kg Total, featuring a stunning 222kg World Record Clean & Jerk.</li>
	                <li><strong>2025 European Championships:</strong> Continued his undefeated streak with a Triple Gold sweep in the Snatch, Clean & Jerk, and Total.</li>
	                <li><strong>2024 Paris Olympics:</strong> Gold Medal & World Record (404kg Total).</li>
	                <li><strong>2024 European Championships:</strong> Gold in Snatch and Clean & Jerk.</li>
	                <li><strong>World Cup Dominance:</strong> Consistent podium finishes, establishing him as the pound-for-pound king of the 89kg class.</li>
                </ul>

